1- Configure smpt in your local host
installations:
$ yum install procmail mailx sendmail sendmail-cf-y
changes in the sendmail.mc
$define(`SMART_HOST',`smpt.google.com')
update
$ m4 sendmail.mc > sendmail.cf
$ systemctl start sendmail
$ mail -s "subject" shivam.sg@sigmoidanalytics.com
> content
> ctrl+d


2-Add user in your local host which cant execute sudo commands
$ adduser username
default users will not have sudo permissions

